comments: Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Simmons' (PHI) path and does not deliver the contact.

Harris (PHI) extends his hand outward and some contact occurs with McConnell's (IND) head as he receives the pass. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Turner (IND) maintains his left foot in-bounds as he receives the pass and starts his dribble.
Howard (PHI) turns into Turner (IND) and initiates body contact during Turner's upward shooting motion.
Harris (PHI) turns slightly as he firms up in his screening position and absorbs the contact made with Brogdon (IND).
McConnell (IND) brings his arm down and makes contact across Thybulle's (PHI) right arm/elbow during the driving shot attempt.
Sabonis' (IND) right foot is outside the plane of his body when marginal foot-to-foot contact occurs with Thybulle (PHI) as the pick is set.
Harris (PHI) and Holiday (IND) engage and disengage both prior to and during the entry pass.
Holiday (IND) is bringing his arm into a vertical position when contact occurs with Harris (PHI) during the shot attempt, which Holiday absorbs.
Sabonis (IND) and Simmons (PHI) engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to obtain rebounding position.
Howard (PHI) cleanly back-taps the ball prior to incidental contact occurring with Sabonis' (IND) backside.
Turner (IND) clamps and holds Howard's (PHI) left arm during rebounding.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Simmons' (PHI) path and turns slightly as the contact occurs, which Sabonis absorbs.
Thybulle (PHI) swipes forward and makes contact with McConnell's (IND) arm prior to making any contact with the ball.
Harris (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Brogdon's (IND) path and turns slightly as the contact occurs, which Harris absorbs.
Sabonis (IND) and Howard (PHI) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Sabonis (IND) has his hand rested on Simmons' (PHI) side and marginal contact occurs as Simmons' momentum carries him beyond the baseline.
Brogdon (IND) and Howard (PHI) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Sabonis (IND) engages and disengages with Howard (PHI) during rebounding.
Korkmaz (PHI) swipes down and makes clean contact with the ball during Brodgon's (IND) driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (IND) and Curry (PHI) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Sabonis (IND) commits the take foul on Curry (PHI).
